Why did Deputy President William Ruto fail to attend the funeral of Nyamira Governor John Nyagarama last week? Well, our source says security officials had been briefed the deputy president was coming and his allies had been facilitated to mobilise people and “soften the ground”. 
Local leaders in his camp were also waiting for him at the funeral, before many of them melted away after realising he would not be joining the mourners. 



