Officials celebrate Sonko ouster
A number of senior City Hall officials, including county executives and chief officers, attended a night party to celebrate the impeachment of their former boss Mike Sonko, a Talk of the Town mole has learnt. 





The night party, which was held at the restaurant of a high-end members’ club in Nairobi, was organised by the pro-impeachment MCAs and kicked off immediately the Senate voted to uphold the ouster of Sonko. 
Interestingly, the senior county officers included those who have been close to the flamboyant city politician. Among the celebrants were also most of the ward representatives who had been ferried to Kwale County by the former Makadara MP.
