Firms threaten to expose governor
A governor in one of the Mount Kenya counties is in trouble. The man has been bragging how his leasing programme has endeared him to the voters. Having been approached by several companies, the governor promised them work on condition they parted with bribes. 
Now having taken bribes from several companies, the work available could only be done by a handful of companies. The companies that missed out are demanding their cash back or else they expose the county executive. 
It seems that 2021 will be a rocky ride for the governor who will be seeking re-election. Here's a list of the people who hit headlines in the biggest way this year. An interdenominational prayer service was held at Nyamira Primary School ahead of tomorrow’s burial. Faiza Wanjiru reveals the tactics used by criminals to target cash-rich revellers. Bishop Kariuki appeals for government assistance to private schools, saying most are currently struggling. Mechanical problem is believed to have been caused by the heavy load and the area’s topography.